what_worked:
Applied decorrelate, date_cte_isolate: ** Extracted the repeated date-filtering subquery into a shared CTE (`filtered_dates`) and converted implicit joins to explicit JOIN syntax. This eliminates redundant computation of the same date logic three times and gives the optimizer better join ordering freedom.

**Expected speedup:** ~1.8-2.5x due to avoiding repeated date subquery execution and improved join planning.
why_it_worked: Correlated subqueries re-execute per outer row; converting to JOIN eliminates per-row overhead; Pre-filtering date dimension into CTE reduces hash join probe table from 73K to ~365 rows
